import java.util.* ;
import java.io.*; 
public class Solution{
	public static boolean possibleToMakeTriangle(ArrayList<Integer> arr){

			Collections.sort(arr);
			int n = arr.size();

			for(int i = 0; i < n-2; i++){
			int a = arr.get(i);
			int b = arr.get(i+1);
			int c = arr.get(i+2);

			if(a + b > c){
				return true;
			}
			}
			
			return false;

	}
}


You are given an integer of array/list 'ARR' of length â€˜N. You are supposed to return true if it is possible to construct at least one non-degenerate triangle using values of
array/list as sides of the triangle, otherwise, return false.
